Mexican Stocks: Grupo Mexico, Modelo Shares Drop; Alfa Advances

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-03-25T21:49:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/mexican-stocks-grupo-mexico-modelo-shares-drop-alfa-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.2 percent to 36,784.27. The gauge
posted its biggest weekly advance since 2009, climbing 3.9
percent.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA MM), the world’s largest producer of
aluminum engine heads, gained 1.7 percent to 152.73 pesos.
Mexico posted a preliminary trade surplus of $274.7 million for
February.  Grupo Modelo SA (GMODELOC MM), the Mexican beermaker that
gets 40 percent of revenue from foreign sales, retreated 0.8
percent to 70.86 pesos after  consumer confidence  dropped in the
U.S. The Thomson Reuters/University of Michigan final index of
consumer sentiment decreased to 67.5, from 77.5 in February, the
group said today.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, fell 1.2 percent to 44.57 pesos. The company was
cut to “hold” from “buy” at Banco Santander SA, analysts led
by Victoria Santaella wrote in a report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
